1. install npm init
2. install npm i express
3. create index.js file
4. create src folder
5. package json add "type":"module" 
6. src folder create folder(routes,service,model,config)
7. install npm i dotenv (import dotenv) & dotenv.config()
8. createfolder .env // not push to git because of personal information
9. createfolder .gitIgnore (use to not push personal information)
10. routes create index.js file => (req,res)
11. routes create index.js import into index.js

mongoosejs.com /docs/validation

1. create employeemodel.js schema construct
2. create src common folder and create file (validation.js)
3. validation.js validate ([stackover](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/18022365/mongoose-validate-email-syntax)) export
4. import validationj.js to employeemodel.js
5. start connection with routes and create file employee.js
6. goto postman app get,post
7. service create employee.js file and import userModel from '../model/employeeModel.js'
8. goto routes and import employeeService from '../service/employee.js'
9. goto routes index.js and import employeeRoutes from './employee.js'
10. postmon post request use
